review_blob: Bottled. Great amber colour. Can taste the amber/caramel malts which give nice aftertaste. Bit flat out of the bottle.
Nice character from Cotswold Springs Brewery. Nice finish to it. Good fruity aroma too.
Top beer. Great bottle conditioned. Bbf are knocking out some great beers at the moment.
I prefer Gem. Good colour to this though. All Bath Ales available in the supermarket are quite similar. Same hops?
Nicer than wild hare. Available in lots of supermarkets. Filtered rather than bottle conditions. Nice hoppy beer. Nothing spectacular.
Citrus and malts. Interesting aftertaste. Grapefruit like. Nice light amber colour to it.
